claim.claim-text:
1. A method of producing an acoustic resonator device, comprising:
depositing a first metal film directly on a substrate;
patterning said first metal film to form an electrode region;
after patterning depositing piezoelectric material on said electrode region to form a single, continuous piezoelectric layer;
depositing a second metal film on said single piezoelectric layer;
patterning said second metal film to form a plurality of spaced apart electrodes; and
removing the piezoelectric material from a region of the piezolelectric layer underneath a spaced apart region between said spaced part electrodes by a selective etching process to limit lateral propagation losses to un-etched regions of the acoustic resonator device, said removing step being performed after said second metal film is patterned.

5. A method of isolating an acoustic resonator device, comprising:
depositing and patterning a first metal film directly on a substrate;
depositing piezoelectric material on said patterned first metal film to form a single, continuous piezoelectric layer;
depositing a second metal film on said single piezoelectric layer;
patterning the second metal film to form a plurality of spaced apart electrodes; and
removing the piezoelectric material from said single piezoelectric layer underlying a spaced apart region between the spaced apart electrodes with a selective etching process to limit propagation of energy in lateral modes, said removing step being performed after said second metal film is deposited on said single piezoelectric layer and patterned.
